      <lg type="edition">
<l>kalañcey kōvē kalañcey kōvē</l>
<l>yaccuṭaic cākāṭ ṭāram poruntiya</l>
<l>ciṟuveṇ palli pōlat taṉṉoṭu</l>
<l>curampala vanta vemakku maruḷi</l>
<l>viyaṉmala rakaṉpoḻi līmat tāḻi</l>
<l>yakali tāka vaṉaimō</l>
<l>naṉantalai mūtūr kalañcey kōvē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Vessel-making king! Vessel-making king! (1)</l>
<l>Being gracious to us too who have come through deserts many (4)</l>
<l>with him resembling a little white gecko (3)</l>
<l>that came close to a spoke of a fearful cart [wheel], (2)</l>
<l>shape the urn for the burial place in the wide grove</l>
<l>with open flowers so that it is wide, (5f.)</l>
<l>o vessel-making king of the old town of vast area. (7)  </l>
</lg>
